    <h2 id="ï¸-project-of-the-day-secure-internal-web-server">ğŸ› ï¸ Project of the Day: â€œSecure Internal Web Serverâ€</h2>
    <p><strong>Scenario:</strong><br />
Youâ€™re asked to deploy a web server that is only accessible from a specific subnet (e.g., 192.168.10.0/24).
<strong>Steps:</strong></p>
    <ol>
      <li>Install <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">apache2</code> (or <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">nginx</code>)</li>
      <li>Set static IP</li>
      <li>Write iptables rules to:</li>
    </ol>
    <ul>
      <li>Allow traffic from 192.168.10.0/24</li>
      <li>Block all other IPs
        <ol>
          <li>Create script to restore rules at boot</li>
          <li>Test from another device or virtual subnet
<strong>Deliverables:</strong></li>
        </ol>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>Markdown: <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">project-secure-webserver.md</code></li>
  <li>Script: <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">restore-firewall.sh</code></li>
  <li>Screenshot: Allowed/denied traffic test
